      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING SAKO (2) flew the lids from out wide with an impressive turn of foot, going on to clock 29.55 when a 3 length winner over 520m at this track last time. Can measure up again. MY BABY BROOKE (3) had a low draw latest where she found trouble and fell over 520m at this track. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the low draw. Rates a key player and gets chance to atone. BANK KEEPING (1) stalked the lead from a middle box before hitting the front turning and lifting to score (29.99) at Richmond in a Mix over 520m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. NOTTS COUNTY (8) didn't live up to the market support last time but cannot be taken lightly.",
